The paper deals with logical fragments and decision problems, which are typical topics in the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of modular predicates and the transfer result may also be relevant to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). The covering problem, which is a more general version of the separation problem, may fall under the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also mentions regular languages, which are studied in the area of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of logic and decision problems may have applications in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
